@startuml
title REQ-016 GPU Auto-Select Sequence

participant "render-video.mjs" as Script
participant "PowerShell" as PS
participant "nvidia-smi" as NSMI
participant "Remotion Launcher" as Launcher
participant "Chrome Headless" as Chrome
participant "ffmpeg" as FFmpeg

== GPU Detection ==

Script -> PS: Get-CimInstance Win32_VideoController
PS --> Script: GPU list (name, vendorId, RAM)

alt PowerShell failed
  Script -> NSMI: nvidia-smi --query-gpu
  NSMI --> Script: NVIDIA GPU info
end

Script -> Script: selectOptimalGpu(gpus)\npriority: NVIDIA > AMD > Intel > iGPU

== Browser Patch ==

Script -> Launcher: monkey-patch launchChrome()
note right of Launcher
  Wrap original function:
  inject GPU args into opts.args
end note

Script -> Script: Set DXGI_GPU_PREFERENCE=2\nSet SHIM_MCCOMPAT=0x800000001

== Encoder Detection ==

Script -> FFmpeg: where ffmpeg
FFmpeg --> Script: ffmpeg path

Script -> FFmpeg: ffmpeg -encoders
FFmpeg --> Script: encoder list

loop for each candidate (vendor-ordered)
  Script -> FFmpeg: test encode (256x256, 0.1s)
  FFmpeg --> Script: success/fail
end

== Print Report ==

Script -> Script: Print GPU Detection Report

== Render (existing flow) ==

Script -> Launcher: launchChrome(opts)\n(patched: extra GPU args)
Launcher -> Chrome: spawn with GPU args
note right of Chrome
  --use-angle=d3d11
  --enable-gpu
  DXGI selects discrete GPU
end note

Chrome --> Launcher: browser instance
Script -> Chrome: renderMedia (frame by frame)
Chrome --> Script: MP4 (CPU-encoded)

== GPU Re-encode (if available) ==

alt GPU encoder detected
  Script -> FFmpeg: re-encode with h264_nvenc/amf/qsv
  FFmpeg --> Script: GPU-encoded MP4
end

@enduml
